229
00:12:22,501 --> 00:12:23,401
Of course.

230
00:12:23,631 --> 00:12:25,761
If a guy like that shows up,
I'd go with him too!

231
00:12:25,971 --> 00:12:27,771
Yeah, I guess.

232
00:12:28,841 --> 00:12:30,701
What makes you so carefree?!

233
00:12:31,011 --> 00:12:33,671
Hey, why are we talking
about me now?

234
00:12:34,981 --> 00:12:37,141
What were you thinking?

235
00:12:39,621 --> 00:12:42,111
You're so easily fooled by others!

236
00:12:42,621 --> 00:12:44,021
I don't think it's a good idea

237
00:12:44,021 --> 00:12:45,391
for you to move in with
a complete stranger!

238
00:12:45,491 --> 00:12:46,051
Shoji!

239
00:12:46,521 --> 00:12:49,361
Jun-chan already said that.
So say something else.

240
00:12:49,461 --> 00:12:51,451
Is that so... Then, let's see...

241
00:12:51,931 --> 00:12:52,621
Sorry.

242
00:12:55,131 --> 00:12:56,261
Okay, I got it.

243
00:12:57,331 --> 00:12:58,891
Let's live together, Nana.

244
00:13:00,701 --> 00:13:04,041
If living alone makes you too nervous,
you can stay here.

245
00:13:04,811 --> 00:13:05,471
But...

246
