248
00:13:11,411 --> 00:13:13,011
No, not that. But you!

249
00:13:13,651 --> 00:13:16,881
You wouldn't wanna live with me.
You'll hate it.

250
00:13:17,621 --> 00:13:20,151
I'm always wanting my own way,
and I whine.

251
00:13:21,061 --> 00:13:22,891
You think I don't know that?

252
00:13:22,891 --> 00:13:24,951
I'm used to it, or rather,
I've given up about that.

253
00:13:25,191 --> 00:13:25,721
How dare you!

254
00:13:26,531 --> 00:13:29,591
Just kidding.
Let's do it, okay?

255
00:13:30,501 --> 00:13:31,191
Shoji...

256
00:13:33,141 --> 00:13:34,031
Thank you.

257
00:13:34,801 --> 00:13:35,631
That makes me happy.

258
00:13:36,571 --> 00:13:37,661
But I can't!

259
00:13:39,111 --> 00:13:41,771
Those words were all
I needed to hear.

260
00:13:42,511 --> 00:13:44,341
You've chosen me over Sachiko.

261
00:13:44,651 --> 00:13:45,581
Who the heck is Sachiko?

262
00:13:46,551 --> 00:13:47,911
You're just too kind.

263
00:13:48,221 --> 00:13:49,451
If we live together,

264
00:13:49,451 --> 00:13:52,351
I'm going to rely on you
too much all the time.

265
00:13:52,991 --> 00:13:55,581
I don't want to be a burden anymore
than I already am.

266
00:13:57,331 --> 00:13:59,021
No, Nana.

267
00:13:59,261 --> 00:14:01,761
Before you go and become
a burden on a complete stranger,

268
00:14:01,761 --> 00:14:02,891
let it be me!

269
00:14:03,101 --> 00:14:07,661
But like, I'm twenty already!
I wanna be a mature woman!

270
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:10,901
A classy woman
the television viewers can idolize!

271
00:14:11,411 --> 00:14:12,901
Please understand!

272
00:14:13,111 --> 00:14:16,811
If at all possible,
that's how I want you to be, too.

273
00:14:17,981 --> 00:14:22,881
Anyway, if you're able to go
and live on your own,

274
00:14:23,491 --> 00:14:25,041
go for it.

275
00:14:26,421 --> 00:14:29,081
Just don't go moving in
with a total stranger.

276
00:14:29,861 --> 00:14:34,091
Why not?
Why doesn't anyone trust Nana?

277
00:14:34,501 --> 00:14:37,701
It's not her that we don't trust.

278
00:14:37,701 --> 00:14:39,531
It's your ability to judge people.

279
00:14:41,341 --> 00:14:43,411
You know Nana, she's beautiful,
has a small face,

280
00:14:43,411 --> 00:14:46,101
she's thin, has a husky voice,
she is sooo cool!

281
00:14:48,811 --> 00:14:51,611
She could be a top star
in a musical.

282
00:14:51,851 --> 00:14:53,181
What's that supposed to mean?

283
00:14:53,521 --> 00:14:56,351
You feel attracted to a person
just by their looks?

284
00:14:56,691 --> 00:14:58,591
You'd like her too, Shoji.

285
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:02,921
But what if you decide that
you like her better than me?!

286
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:05,251
I couldn't go on living!

287
00:15:08,531 --> 00:15:10,121
All right. Introduce her to me.

288
00:15:10,601 --> 00:15:12,401
I'll go to the apartment
with you tomorrow.

289
00:15:12,501 --> 00:15:13,731
You promise
you won't fall in love with her?

290
00:15:13,901 --> 00:15:17,301
I promise. I've got my hands full
with you and Sachiko.

291
00:15:18,341 --> 00:15:22,301
Oh yeah, that's right.
Sachiko is quite a wild woman.

292
00:15:22,511 --> 00:15:24,041
You'll never make it.

293
00:15:24,581 --> 00:15:26,341
So who the heck is Sachiko!

294
00:15:33,261 --> 00:15:35,461
I was wondering what kind of an old
rundown shack you were gonna show me,

295
00:15:35,461 --> 00:15:37,051
but this is pretty nice.

296
00:15:39,561 --> 00:15:42,121
Seventy thousand yen for
this place is a good deal.

297
00:15:42,571 --> 00:15:43,731
Maybe it's haunted.

298
00:15:43,931 --> 00:15:45,531
What do you mean by that?!

299
00:15:45,871 --> 00:15:47,131
Never mind that.

300
00:15:47,441 --> 00:15:49,061
Why did you guys come here
with us?

301
00:15:49,341 --> 00:15:50,831
Why not?

302
00:15:51,311 --> 00:15:53,511
Besides, I wanna get
a look at that girl

303
00:15:53,511 --> 00:15:55,501
who has the guts to live with Nana.

304
00:15:55,681 --> 00:15:57,941
Courtesy call.
We're representing the benefactors.

305
00:15:58,581 --> 00:16:01,181
So, where's your room?

306
00:16:02,151 --> 00:16:03,481
Room 707.

307
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:05,121
707?!

308
00:16:05,221 --> 00:16:05,321
That's bad luck!

309
00:16:05,321 --> 00:16:05,991
Demon Lord
That's bad luck!

310
00:16:06,161 --> 00:16:08,891
Since when have you guys
become believers of the Demon Lord?

311
00:16:12,701 --> 00:16:15,891
There's no answer.
Maybe Nana's not here yet.

312
00:16:16,371 --> 00:16:17,331
Do you have a key?

313
00:16:17,801 --> 00:16:19,061
I haven't been given one yet.

314
00:16:19,171 --> 00:16:21,601
Why not?
You have a contract, right?

315
00:16:21,801 --> 00:16:25,581
Yeah, but I needed a guarantor
to sign and seal it,

316
00:16:25,581 --> 00:16:27,041
so I asked my Dad.

317
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:28,771
I should get it tomorrow.

318
00:16:29,111 --> 00:16:32,281
So you're not an official resident yet?

319
00:16:32,481 --> 00:16:34,421
But I already paid
the commission and stuff.

320
00:16:34,551 --> 00:16:35,451
What the?!

321
00:16:35,821 --> 00:16:37,221
Someone's pulling one over on you!

322
00:16:52,171 --> 00:16:53,261
And who might you be?

323
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:56,561
W-Wrong door! I'm very sorry!

324
00:16:56,671 --> 00:16:57,501
I don't believe it!

325
00:16:58,171 --> 00:17:00,041
Cripes! How can you
make such a mistake?

326
00:17:00,241 --> 00:17:03,301
It's cold!
Yasu, what is this place!

327
00:17:03,411 --> 00:17:04,671
There's no hot water!

328
00:17:05,381 --> 00:17:06,711
Maybe this is the right place!

329
00:17:07,181 --> 00:17:07,811
What the hell?

330
00:17:08,451 --> 00:17:10,921
Did you get the gas man to come
and open the valve?

331
00:17:11,691 --> 00:17:12,521
Open what?

332
00:17:13,021 --> 00:17:13,651
Nana!

333
00:17:14,521 --> 00:17:16,421
Nana! I've been waiting for you.

334
00:17:17,431 --> 00:17:18,261
What took you so long?

335
00:17:18,831 --> 00:17:20,021
Nana, get dressed.

336
00:17:20,901 --> 00:17:22,491
Oh, is your boyfriend with you?

337
00:17:22,631 --> 00:17:24,271
- Mhm, my friends are here too.
- Hey, she might just be my type.

338
00:17:24,271 --> 00:17:25,961
- Come on in.
- That's nice.

339
00:17:26,241 --> 00:17:27,901
Man, it's cold!

340
00:17:28,171 --> 00:17:29,401
I'm going to catch cold!

341
00:17:29,471 --> 00:17:31,961
What are you gonna do for me
if I lose my beautiful voice?!

342
00:17:32,981 --> 00:17:35,171
Please. So you are
the other occupant.

343
00:17:35,481 --> 00:17:37,971
Yes! Th-Th-Thank you
for welcoming us in!

344
00:17:38,081 --> 00:17:41,641
What's the hesitation?
This is your place, too.

345
00:17:42,621 --> 00:17:45,221
How do you do?
My name is Junko Saotome.

346
00:17:45,221 --> 00:17:46,811
I'm a friend of Nana Komatsu.

347
00:17:47,391 --> 00:17:48,451
Who are you?

348
00:17:48,661 --> 00:17:50,151
She's got guts.

349
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:54,491
Oh, pardon me for
not introducing myself earlier.

350
00:17:55,161 --> 00:17:58,501
I'm a friend of Nana Osaki,
Yasushi Takagi by name.

351
00:17:58,631 --> 00:18:00,001
I am also her acting benefactor.

352
00:18:01,071 --> 00:18:01,931
Nice to meet you.

353
00:18:02,071 --> 00:18:03,471
Yasushi Takagi
Ishizuka Law Office

354
00:18:03,571 --> 00:18:04,871
Law Firm?!

355
00:18:05,011 --> 00:18:06,201
- A lawyer?
- Really?

356
00:18:06,611 --> 00:18:08,041
I'm still learning,

357
00:18:08,041 --> 00:18:10,911
but if you're ever in trouble,
feel free to give me a call.

358
00:18:12,351 --> 00:18:14,151
Then why don't you
do something about this, Yasu?

359
00:18:14,151 --> 00:18:16,121
I'm in trouble
because I have no hot water.

360
00:18:16,491 --> 00:18:19,661
So you gotta call the gas company
to get a guy over here to open up...

361
00:18:19,661 --> 00:18:20,681
You call.

362
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:24,021
Yes ma'am.
Let's see. The number...

363
00:18:24,131 --> 00:18:26,221
Well then.
Perhaps I'll make some tea.

364
00:18:26,931 --> 00:18:28,121
Let me help.

365
00:18:28,401 --> 00:18:30,401
Hey, do you have a kettle
and cups and stuff?

366
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:31,661
- Nope.
- You good for nothing!

367
00:18:31,731 --> 00:18:32,791
I'm sorry!

368
00:18:32,971 --> 00:18:34,771
You gotta wait for
the gas guy to come

369
00:18:34,771 --> 00:18:36,101
before you can use
the burner anyway!

370
00:18:36,441 --> 00:18:37,671
Oh, that's right.

371
00:18:37,771 --> 00:18:39,211
You've gotta do that?

372
00:18:39,311 --> 00:18:40,711
So did you call them?

373
00:18:41,111 --> 00:18:42,201
The line was busy.

374
00:18:42,711 --> 00:18:45,511
Also, fill this in and send it
to the power company.

375
00:18:46,351 --> 00:18:48,921
Your water bill will be debited from
your bank account along with your rent,

376
00:18:48,921 --> 00:18:50,411
so you don't have to worry about those.

377
00:18:51,151 --> 00:18:53,381
Oh, and don't forget to register
your new address with the City Hall.

378
00:18:54,121 --> 00:18:56,221
Well Nana,
I guess we'll be leaving, then.

379
00:18:56,791 --> 00:18:59,351
Looks like we can trust this guy
to look after things for you.

380
00:18:59,801 --> 00:19:00,781
We can?

381
00:19:00,861 --> 00:19:02,331
Well, hang in there, man.

382
00:19:02,731 --> 00:19:04,391
Oh, are you leaving so soon?

383
00:19:06,901 --> 00:19:08,371
The child doesn't know left
from right,

384
00:19:08,371 --> 00:19:10,241
but I hope you do befriend her.

385
00:19:10,371 --> 00:19:11,701
The pleasure is ours.

386
00:19:13,881 --> 00:19:16,811
Shoji, are you coming?
You're working tonight, right?

387
00:19:16,981 --> 00:19:19,241
Right. What should I do?

388
00:19:19,821 --> 00:19:22,151
Don't worry about me, Shoji.

389
00:19:22,551 --> 00:19:24,421
Nana is here too, so I'll be okay.

390
00:19:24,521 --> 00:19:25,421
That's right.

391
00:19:25,621 --> 00:19:29,351
Shoji, you...
be a man and go earn some money.

392
00:19:30,991 --> 00:19:32,821
Well, it may be all right.

393
00:19:33,331 --> 00:19:37,491
That lawyer, Takagi, is taking care
of the other Nana and our Nana too.

394
00:19:38,071 --> 00:19:41,871
The two of them seem to be
getting along just fine.

395
00:19:42,241 --> 00:19:43,401
Like, both placing herself above all?

396
00:19:44,171 --> 00:19:47,771
The other Nana seems
even weirder than our Nana.

397
00:19:47,941 --> 00:19:49,741
Stop repeating Nana
and Nana so much.

398
00:19:50,051 --> 00:19:52,481
I feel my troubles doubling.

399
00:19:53,021 --> 00:19:56,041
Two times seven is fourteen.
Seven squared is forty-nine.

400
00:19:56,991 --> 00:19:58,421
- My troubles are gonna multiply.
- As such...

401
00:19:58,421 --> 00:20:02,551
Nana and I started living together
on a positive note.

402
00:20:03,561 --> 00:20:05,491
At least for me, that is.

403
00:20:07,061 --> 00:20:09,901
Nana, the soonest the gas company people
can make it here is tomorrow.

404
00:20:10,031 --> 00:20:13,521
No way! Then we can't even heat
this place until then?

405
00:20:14,001 --> 00:20:15,801
You don't even have
an air conditioner here.

406
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:16,731
No way!

407
00:20:17,011 --> 00:20:18,631
If you're cold,
put on something warm.

408
00:20:19,081 --> 00:20:21,441
But I only brought my leather jacket.

409
00:20:22,111 --> 00:20:22,981
I can't get comfortable in that.

410
00:20:23,951 --> 00:20:25,381
Oh, do you want me
to lend you something?

411
00:20:25,981 --> 00:20:28,311
Really? Thanks. Thanks a lot.

412
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:32,191
When I first arrived in Tokyo,

413
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:35,311
I didn't know whether
I'd be able to make it or not.

414
00:20:35,691 --> 00:20:38,351
Could I get a job,
would I be Shoji's girl forever?

415
00:20:38,831 --> 00:20:40,801
I had a mountain of anxieties.

416
00:20:44,101 --> 00:20:47,131
Your bag's all clothes.
Are you a peddler?

417
00:20:48,341 --> 00:20:50,171
What's your choice, ma'am?

418
00:20:51,441 --> 00:20:54,341
But as strange as it seems,

419
00:20:54,341 --> 00:20:56,541
I had absolutely no qualms about
moving in with you, Nana.

420
00:20:58,681 --> 00:21:03,141
It's hard to explain why.
That's just how it was.

421
00:21:07,191 --> 00:21:12,181
I reached into the sky

422
00:21:12,291 --> 00:21:18,701
But I couldn't reach what I wanted

423
00:21:18,901 --> 00:21:24,071
They grew smaller
and disappeared into the sky

424
00:21:24,071 --> 00:21:30,071
Like colorful balloons

425
00:21:30,251 --> 00:21:32,181
I'm alone

426
00:21:32,181 --> 00:21:35,911
My hand had no place to go

427
00:21:36,091 --> 00:21:42,551
And gently you took it

428
00:21:42,661 --> 00:21:43,731
Starless night

429
00:21:43,731 --> 00:21:47,921
I won't look back
at the shadow of my past

430
00:21:48,161 --> 00:21:53,731
I want to feel your warmth

431
00:21:54,341 --> 00:21:55,601
Tears are falling down

432
00:21:55,601 --> 00:21:59,701
Even if I'm unsure I won't let go

433
00:21:59,781 --> 00:22:06,201
Of your hand holding mine

